---
// ============================================================
// SMALL BUSINESS HUB — custom pipelines, an AI that learns
// your business and optimizes for the stop-loss.
// Grounded in what's shipped: RAPID²AI (hospitality) and the
// binding-constraint method in the worker.
// ============================================================
import '~/assets/styles/hub.css';
import Layout from '~/layouts/Layout.astro';
import HubNav from '~/components/hub/HubNav.astro';
import HubFooter from '~/components/hub/HubFooter.astro';

const metadata = {
  title: 'Small Business Hub — The Ethical Intelligence Project',
  description:
    'Custom-built intelligence pipelines for small operators: an AI that learns your business, watches where the money actually leaks, and optimizes for the stop-loss before the growth spend.',
};
---

<Layout metadata={metadata}>
  <div class="eih">
    <HubNav current="/business" />

    <!-- HERO -->
    <section class="hero wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow rv">The Small Business Hub</div>
      <h1>An AI that learns your business — and stops the bleeding first.</h1>
      <p class="lede">
        Most tools sell you growth. We start at the other end: <strong>the stop-loss</strong>. Before you spend a dollar
        chasing new revenue, a custom-built pipeline learns how your operation actually runs, finds where money is
        quietly leaking, and closes that leak — because a dollar you stop losing is worth exactly as much as a dollar
        you earn, and it's usually far easier to get.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Talk to us about your operation</a>
        <a href="#how" class="btn ghost">How the pipeline works</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- HOW -->
    <section id="how" class="wrap">
      <div class="eyebrow rv">How it works</div>
      <h2 class="rv">Built for your operation. Not a template.</h2>
      <div class="cards four rv stagger">
        <div class="card">
          <div class="n">01 · LEARN</div>
          <h3>It learns your business</h3>
          <p>
            Your invoices, your menu or product mix, your point-of-sale, your costs. The pipeline is built around the
            data you already generate — nothing new to maintain.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="n">02 · WATCH</div>
          <h3>It watches the variance</h3>
          <p>
            Every week it compares what things should cost with what they actually cost — price creep from suppliers,
            portion drift, margin erosion — the leaks too small to see and too expensive to ignore.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="n">03 · NAME</div>
          <h3>It names the one bottleneck</h3>
          <p>
            Not a dashboard with forty charts. One finding: the single constraint costing you the most right now, how
            confident we are, and the smallest concrete move that fixes or tests it.
          </p>
        </div>
        <div class="card">
          <div class="n">04 · OPTIMIZE</div>
          <h3>Then it compounds</h3>
          <p>
            Clear one constraint and the next one becomes visible. The pipeline keeps learning your rhythms, so the
            stop-loss keeps tightening while you run the business.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- PROOF -->
    <section class="wrap">
      <div class="split rv">
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow rv">Already running</div>
          <h2 class="rv">Proven inside the hardest margin business there is.</h2>
          <p>
            This isn't a pitch deck. The first of these pipelines — <strong>RAPID²AI</strong> — runs today in hospitality:
            live food-cost tracking, price-variance alerts on every invoice line, menu and POS intelligence, built from inside
            an industry that runs on margin and instinct.
          </p>
          <p>
            The Small Business Hub takes the same architecture — learn the operation, watch the variance, name the
            constraint — and builds it custom for yours: retail, trades, farm operations, professional services,
            anywhere the books hide a leak.
          </p>
          <div class="cta-row" style="justify-content:flex-start">
            <a href="https://rapidai.pages.dev/coo/" target="_blank" rel="noreferrer" class="btn ghost">
              See RAPID²AI live →
            </a>
          </div>
        </div>
        <div>
          <div class="eyebrow rv">What a custom pipeline includes</div>
          <div class="limit-list rv">
            <div class="limit-row"><span class="k">Data intake</span><span class="v">your existing systems</span></div>
            <div class="limit-row">
              <span class="k">Variance watch</span><span class="v">continuous, automated</span>
            </div>
            <div class="limit-row">
              <span class="k">Constraint report</span><span class="v">one finding, weekly</span>
            </div>
            <div class="limit-row">
              <span class="k">Ask-anything access</span><span class="v">Elle, on your data</span>
            </div>
            <div class="limit-row"><span class="k">Pricing</span><span class="v">scoped to the operation</span></div>
          </div>
          <p style="font-size:0.85rem;margin-top:14px">
            Custom builds are scoped per operation — tell us what you run and we'll tell you what the pipeline looks
            like and what it costs. Beta-era clients keep their pricing indefinitely.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- CTA -->
    <section class="wrap" style="text-align:center">
      <h2 class="rv">Start with the leak, not the pitch.</h2>
      <p style="max-width:520px;margin:0 auto 26px">
        Tell us what you run — a restaurant, a shop, a farm, a practice — and we'll show you where a pipeline would look
        first.
      </p>
      <div class="cta-row">
        <a href="/contact" class="btn">Get in touch</a>
        <a href="/elle" class="btn ghost">Ask Elle about it first</a>
      </div>
    </section>

    <HubFooter />
  </div>
</Layout>
